<paragraph blockId="19.[813,1457,1339,1498]" box="[813,903,1339,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[813,1457,1339,1498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">
Perrier’s 
<typeStatus box="[907,954,1372,1398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">type</typeStatus>
specimen shares all the characteristics of the common west Indian Ocean species 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Blainville" authorityYear="1830" box="[1197,1380,1405,1431]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Protoreaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="276" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lincki">
<emphasis box="[1197,1380,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">Protoreaster lincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having laterally projecting red tipped spines on some of the distal supero-marginal plates.
</paragraph>
